{
  "stem": "3022.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Because the German-Russian war broke out in June of 1941, and this is a year later.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Upon arrival to the camp, to the camp, they tried to set up a, a, independent council, similar to what used to exist in Jewish towns, like a Kehilla.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So from each group, people gave representatives, you know, to be on this council.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The, the camp was run at, that time, by, by a Polish name-- by a Polish man of name of Falerowski, who, the first thing that he checked out were any valuables, when you came in.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They'd search you and try to-- took the valuables away.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The security of the, of the camp was the-- was the head of the security for the Heinkelwerke, a man by the name of Stein.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "The camp was guarded by the [NON-ENGLISH], which is the industrial, industrial guards that, that lived outside the camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "The work was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Wasn't as difficult as, probably, as in other places, because those who were fortunate to work in the, in the, in the, in the inside the factory, and those with skills, those skills were needed.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I don't know, I haven't heard many people speak about it, it's a little known fact, but the Germans categorized, you know, the, the Jewish workers in three categories.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "There was-- and we were wearing a, a, a sign was the letter R, which mean which meant [NON-ENGLISH], defense work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "There were also Z, which was civilian workers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And A, for army.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "You know, they work for the army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we were so-- probably, in the, in the papers, you know, that the Germans kept, all marked as [NON-ENGLISH], defense workers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I worked on a, on a seven-foot long break that-- we bended metals.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
